{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# S2 — Deploy Gerrit + rebar MCP (docker-compose) behind nginx + TLS\n\n## Why\nRun Gerrit and the rebar MCP as the two containers on the box, reachable over HTTPS at\n`rebar.solutions.navateam.com`. Gerrit needs a `%2F`-safe reverse proxy — the community\nuses nginx/Apache, NOT Caddy (Caddy URL-decodes paths by default with no global switch,\nwhich breaks Gerrit's change/project screens; no confirmed Caddy+Gerrit recipe exists).\n\n## What\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`:\n  - official `gerritcodereview/gerrit` pinned to a PATCH tag (e.g. `3.14.1`) with\n    persistent volumes (git/index/cache/etc/db on the data volume) + the two-step init.\n    DERISK NOTE (E4): the bare minor tags `3.14`/`3.13` do NOT exist on Docker Hub; pin a\n    published patch tag (`3.14.1`/`3.13.7`/`3.12.8`), all of which publish arm64 manifests.\n  - the `rebar-mcp` container (`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM=1`, signing key + ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n    from the boot `.env`, write-gating as needed); both `restart: unless-stopped`, pinned tags.\n- `gerrit.config`: `container.heapLimit=2g` with `core.packedGitLimit` budgeted INSIDE the\n  heap (~512m-1g), NoteDb, `canonicalWebUrl=https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/`, sshd/httpd\n  thread caps + `sshd.batchThreads` to avoid parallel-clone OOM.\n- nginx + certbot (Let's Encrypt) terminating TLS on 443: route Gerrit (`%2F`-safe:\n  `proxy_pass` with no path) and the MCP webhook/vote endpoint behind the one cert; Gerrit\n  SSH passthrough on 29418.\n\n## Scope\nIn: containers, volumes, base `gerrit.config`, nginx+TLS, MCP hosting. Out: Gerrit\nproject/label/submit-req (S3), bot identity + event wiring (S4), replication (S5).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`, `infra/compose/gerrit.config`, `infra/nginx/*.conf`,\n  bootstrap scripts under `infra/`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Gerrit reachable at `https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/` with a valid Let's Encrypt cert;\n      a change screen / a project path containing `%2F` renders correctly (encoded-slash round-trip verified).\n- [ ] Gerrit SSH clone works on 29418; the admin account is bootstrapped; data persists across\n      `docker compose down/up` and an instance reboot (`restart: unless-stopped`).\n- [ ] The rebar MCP container runs co-located and is reachable through nginx, with its signing key\n      + ANTHROPIC_API_KEY sourced from SSM (never baked into the image/compose).\n- [ ] Gerrit runs a supported version at an EXISTING arm64 patch tag (e.g.\n      `gerritcodereview/gerrit:3.14.1`; a bare minor tag like `3.14` is NOT used — it doesn't exist);\n      `heapLimit=2g` with `packedGitLimit` budgeted within it."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782686142450675001,"uuid":"833a2296-2401-424a-b7fd-ea3db1918dc0"}